1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,740
[All characters, behaviors, locations,
organizations, professions, and events

2
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:07,490
shown in this series are entirely fictional,
created solely for entertainment purposes,

3
00:00:07,510 --> 00:00:11,250
with no intention of instructing
or endorsing any kind of behaviors;

4
00:00:11,270 --> 00:00:15,000
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:18,830
A clover leaf?

6
00:00:20,330 --> 00:00:21,760
I thought you said you can't remember me.

7
00:00:26,350 --> 00:00:28,290
I think that perhaps love

8
00:00:28,330 --> 00:00:30,730
is the memory of a time

9
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:31,850
when we were happy.

10
00:00:31,890 --> 00:00:35,520
A reminder that you used to be
a crucial part of someone's life.

11
00:00:37,060 --> 00:00:38,920
Have you ever felt
like that toward someone?

12
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:41,600
Because that person
hasn't realized just yet

13
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:43,920
that he is someone important to me.

14
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:53,860
And what about you?

15
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:56,080
What role do you play

16
00:00:56,650 --> 00:00:58,320
on this board?

17
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:01,290
I'm tired of being compared
to a pawn by others.

18
00:01:03,190 --> 00:01:05,230
I'll be the hand that moves the pieces now.

19
00:01:47,860 --> 00:01:49,289
I have a job for you all.

20
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:15,770
♫But no one sees what's behind my smiles♫

21
00:02:16,190 --> 00:02:19,829
♫It's the loneliness I try to hide♫

22
00:02:19,860 --> 00:02:25,220
♫Will there be someone my heart's seeking?♫

23
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:29,090
♫Then today, I got you near♫

24
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:33,870
♫You made my heart drift away,♫

25
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:35,850
♫lost in your gaze♫

26
00:02:36,180 --> 00:02:39,329
♫Like a stream washing over me♫

27
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:44,810
♫Wanna give this a try,
like it’s more than one night?♫

28
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:48,420
♫Let's change one night into♫

29
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:50,240
♫something more, alright♫

30
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:53,390
♫Let's follow our hearts once♫

31
00:02:53,450 --> 00:02:59,280
♫Wanna give this a try, just let me get inside?♫

32
00:02:59,340 --> 00:03:05,500
♫Deep inside, I'll make you feel whole♫

33
00:03:05,740 --> 00:03:10,080
♫May I ask you to be my last?♫

34
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:35,840
Gale.

35
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:37,710
Is the size okay now?

36
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:39,200
Or does it need any adjustment?

37
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:41,020
Mm...

38
00:03:43,130 --> 00:03:45,400
I think it looks good on the model now.

39
00:03:46,450 --> 00:03:48,900
The mannequin just makes it look off.

40
00:03:49,090 --> 00:03:50,090
Hm...

41
00:03:53,450 --> 00:03:54,490
What's your height, Phae?

42
00:03:55,010 --> 00:03:55,850
160 cm.

43
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:56,810
Why?

44
00:03:58,540 --> 00:03:59,780
You're about the same height
as the model.

45
00:04:01,690 --> 00:04:03,880
Can you try on the dress instead?

46
00:04:07,030 --> 00:04:07,900
Sure.

47
00:04:11,430 --> 00:04:12,890
Do I have to take my shirt off?

48
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:14,680
What? No.

49
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:16,700
There's no need.

50
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:19,010
I thought you wanted it to be exact.

51
00:04:19,850 --> 00:04:20,860
Are you crazy?

52
00:04:23,750 --> 00:04:26,160
Your shirt is so small.
It won't make a difference.

53
00:04:26,210 --> 00:04:26,990
Well,

54
00:04:27,030 --> 00:04:28,240
I was just asking.

55
00:04:29,010 --> 00:04:29,890
Excuse me.

56
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:35,520
Looks like the shoulders
are wider by an inch.

57
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,360
Hey,

58
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:38,570
it's only by an inch.

59
00:04:38,710 --> 00:04:39,790
So it should be alright.

60
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,600
Or else it would be too tight
when the model wears it.

61
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:46,620
If it's for sale,

62
00:04:46,650 --> 00:04:48,280
I think you can do that.

63
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:51,590
But this is the first showcase,

64
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:54,140
so I think it needs to fit the model perfectly

65
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:55,890
to achieve the best look.

66
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:58,040
Oh...

67
00:04:58,310 --> 00:04:59,409
So that's why

68
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:01,950
famous designers are very serious

69
00:05:01,980 --> 00:05:03,630
when they're casting models.

70
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,590
Yeah.

71
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,960
I'll be measuring your bust size next.

72
00:05:12,030 --> 00:05:13,500
I didn't mean it like that.

73
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:15,810
I'm just saying that...

74
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,520
It's fine.

75
00:05:18,150 --> 00:05:19,790
Why are you always correcting yourself?

76
00:05:21,050 --> 00:05:22,810
Well, I worded it badly.

77
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:24,290
I didn't want to cause any misunderstanding.

78
00:05:26,610 --> 00:05:27,870
Can you lift your hair up?

79
00:05:28,210 --> 00:05:29,720
- It's in the way.
- Oh.

80
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,040
Gale.

81
00:05:44,390 --> 00:05:45,390
Gale.

82
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,120
Gale?

83
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,320
Are you okay?

84
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:53,500
It's nothing.

85
00:06:00,150 --> 00:06:02,800
This is my first time seeing you
wearing this bracelet.

86
00:06:05,410 --> 00:06:06,410
Oh.

87
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:08,180
You mean this?

88
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,610
Mm...

89
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,360
Someone gave it to me
back when I was still in Paris.

90
00:06:13,210 --> 00:06:15,020
Yesterday I cleaned up...

91
00:06:15,380 --> 00:06:16,420
and found it.

92
00:06:18,670 --> 00:06:19,610
It's pretty, right?

93
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:23,980
I think it suits me.

94
00:06:26,510 --> 00:06:28,190
The person who gave me this
probably has a fashion sense.

95
00:06:31,810 --> 00:06:32,510
Yeah.

96
00:06:33,290 --> 00:06:34,500
It suits you.

97
00:06:37,110 --> 00:06:39,200
If you got it back when you were in Paris,

98
00:06:41,490 --> 00:06:43,020
why are you only wearing it now?

99
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:49,920
Well...

100
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:52,300
I just wanted to prove something.

101
00:06:53,810 --> 00:06:55,380
And it looks like I got the answer.

102
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:02,860
I got your measurements.

103
00:07:03,020 --> 00:07:03,400
And...

104
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:05,290
there's no need for any adjustment.

105
00:07:05,970 --> 00:07:07,890
Maybe I have to trim the shoulders a bit.

106
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:10,590
I'll handle the rest.

107
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:12,220
Okay.

108
00:07:16,590 --> 00:07:17,590
Gale,

109
00:07:17,660 --> 00:07:19,560
I have to go to the city with my mom.

110
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:21,380
And about the accessories,

111
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:23,300
I already drafted a few ideas.

112
00:07:23,420 --> 00:07:24,500
After you see them,

113
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:27,120
tell me how you feel,
and I'll take care of it, okay?

114
00:07:27,210 --> 00:07:28,390
Okay.

115
00:07:28,630 --> 00:07:30,440
Then I'll see you later.

116
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:31,460
See you later.

117
00:08:25,210 --> 00:08:25,860
Auntie,

118
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,280
the fact that Boss called a sudden meeting,

119
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:29,840
does it mean there's
something bad going on?

120
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:30,880
Right?

121
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:33,169
Boss seems a bit tense, too.

122
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:35,919
I think most of you already know

123
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:39,799
that we're focusing
on improving our crop yields

124
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,940
in order to enter into a contract with K Group,

125
00:08:42,970 --> 00:08:44,830
our partner in South Korea.

126
00:08:47,460 --> 00:08:49,200
Is it not going
according to plan?

127
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,140
Are they not going to cooperate with us?

128
00:08:54,420 --> 00:08:55,320
Well,

129
00:08:58,210 --> 00:08:59,210
we are...

130
00:09:12,270 --> 00:09:13,410
We're about to seal the deal!

131
00:09:21,050 --> 00:09:22,280
That scared me.

132
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:24,760
Oh, Boss.

133
00:09:25,010 --> 00:09:27,200
You made me so nervous there, Boss.

134
00:09:27,230 --> 00:09:29,210
I thought something
terrible had happened again.

135
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:32,490
If I just said it normally,
it would be boring.

136
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:33,490
I was scared for a second.

137
00:09:33,530 --> 00:09:35,640
The reason I called everyone here

138
00:09:35,790 --> 00:09:37,720
is that I wanted to
tell you the good news.

139
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:40,520
And since we're about to be able
to seal the deal,

140
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,840
I'd like to treat you all to a meal

141
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:45,260
for your hard work at Phusangdao Farm.

142
00:09:45,810 --> 00:09:47,470
I'll tell the caterer to prepare a lot of food

143
00:09:47,510 --> 00:09:49,280
and drinks for all of you.

144
00:09:49,610 --> 00:09:51,480
Let's finish work early today

145
00:09:51,580 --> 00:09:52,660
to celebrate!

146
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:04,680
Our boss is the best!

147
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:07,260
I pray that in the next life,

148
00:10:07,340 --> 00:10:10,750
I get to work as your subordinate again,

149
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,170
forevermore.

150
00:10:12,220 --> 00:10:13,440
Come on, Paula.

151
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:14,890
Have you asked Boss

152
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,320
if he wanted to
meet you in his next life?

153
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,440
What about it, huh?

154
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,610
You!

155
00:10:19,610 --> 00:10:20,840
Everyone,

156
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:23,520
let's get back to work, shall we?

157
00:10:24,130 --> 00:10:25,640
I'll see you tonight.

158
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:27,130
And have fun,

159
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:28,400
alright?

160
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,400
- Okay.
- Then go back to work.

161
00:10:32,140 --> 00:10:33,980
Go, let's go!

162
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:36,500
Go, go, let's go.

163
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:39,810
Party, party.

164
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:40,600
We're going to party.

165
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,080
I'm a heavyweight drinker, you know?

166
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,230
I don't believe you!

167
00:10:44,940 --> 00:10:45,900
See you.

168
00:10:53,570 --> 00:10:55,090
You're not going to bring your hat?

169
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:57,500
It's Auntie Nong's.

170
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:24,480
What are you doing?

171
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,090
I'm trying to help you.

172
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:45,300
What?!

173
00:11:45,570 --> 00:11:46,410
Hey!

174
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:47,660
You brats!

175
00:11:47,780 --> 00:11:48,360
Mok!

176
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:50,200
Come pick these up, Saeng.

177
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,450
Mok! Saeng!

178
00:11:53,820 --> 00:11:55,490
These damn brats.

179
00:11:57,170 --> 00:11:59,690
And I'm the one who has to
clean up their mess.

180
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:01,610
They're blending in with the grass,

181
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,750
so they're even harder to find.

182
00:12:09,150 --> 00:12:09,770
Wait,

183
00:12:11,190 --> 00:12:14,050
did you change
your eyebrow pencil today, Paula?

184
00:12:16,730 --> 00:12:18,840
You can just say that I'm pretty.

185
00:12:21,610 --> 00:12:22,230
It looks ridiculous.

186
00:12:22,260 --> 00:12:23,180
Hey, you!

187
00:12:23,930 --> 00:12:25,840
Yes, you're the prettiest of them all.

188
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:26,900
Ugh.

189
00:12:27,190 --> 00:12:28,580
Your hair is this short,

190
00:12:28,620 --> 00:12:30,600
so don't you judge a lady like me.

191
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:32,240
Well, if people with long hair are pretty,

192
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:33,440
then hermits are pretty too, yeah?!

193
00:12:33,470 --> 00:12:35,030
- Hey.
- Ouch.

194
00:12:35,780 --> 00:12:37,280
Am I not beautiful?

195
00:12:37,310 --> 00:12:38,310
Jeez!

196
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:39,530
Kind of.

197
00:12:39,580 --> 00:12:41,200
That doesn't mean
you're pretty, though.

198
00:12:41,540 --> 00:12:42,750
Like Paula here?

199
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:45,360
Even if she's pretty,
no one would want her.

200
00:12:45,860 --> 00:12:47,180
Hey, Auntie,

201
00:12:47,220 --> 00:12:49,110
how can you say that?

202
00:12:49,470 --> 00:12:51,520
I will definitely find my lover.

203
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,290
Mark my words.

204
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:57,530
You all soon will have to
attend my wedding ceremony.

205
00:12:57,710 --> 00:13:00,080
Right, guys?
You think I'll definitely find a lover, right?

206
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:00,930
Really?

207
00:13:01,540 --> 00:13:02,950
Hey, aren't you my friends?

208
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:03,690
Alright, alright.

209
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:05,790
To be honest,

210
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,550
you're very beautiful, Paula.

211
00:13:07,940 --> 00:13:08,940
But...

212
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:13,410
if you shave your eyebrows
a bit sharper,

213
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,200
put on a little more blush,

214
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:17,310
and apply some lipstick,

215
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,680
you can be even more alluring.

216
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:21,720
Right?

217
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:23,360
Isn't this enough?

218
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:25,410
Come, come, right here.

219
00:13:26,130 --> 00:13:26,770
What?

220
00:13:26,810 --> 00:13:28,190
- Sit, sit.
- Ow, ow.

221
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:33,700
Come here.

222
00:13:34,330 --> 00:13:35,330
What?

223
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,720
Hey! What are you doing?

224
00:13:36,780 --> 00:13:37,860
Are you trying to
remove my makeup?

225
00:13:37,890 --> 00:13:38,960
Don't do that.

226
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,800
Sit still.

227
00:13:40,850 --> 00:13:41,850
Come closer.

228
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:46,050
Here, let me... Oh, hey!

229
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,000
How about this...

230
00:13:52,990 --> 00:13:53,990
Here.

231
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:00,070
Well...

232
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,010
The eyebrow tail kinda looks better.

233
00:14:05,390 --> 00:14:06,390
Yeah.

234
00:14:09,610 --> 00:14:10,610
Then,

235
00:14:10,970 --> 00:14:11,970
are you free this evening?

236
00:14:13,740 --> 00:14:14,740
I'll go visit your place.

237
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:16,910
I'm available.

238
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:19,370
I can't.

239
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,310
- I really can't stand it.
- What?

240
00:14:20,350 --> 00:14:21,880
Let me do the other one too.

241
00:14:22,530 --> 00:14:24,620
I have worn my makeup like this
for years now.

242
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:25,810
Quit blabbering.

243
00:14:25,940 --> 00:14:27,410
Let me do the other eyebrow for you.

244
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:32,840
[Phusangdao Group]

245
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,520
It will be settled tonight.

246
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:38,820
Everything will go according to our plan.

247
00:14:49,450 --> 00:14:50,560
What are you doing, Mr. Chakkrit?

248
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:01,600
Ms. Wipa.

249
00:15:03,490 --> 00:15:05,190
Please stay and celebrate with us tonight.

250
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:08,160
I'm throwing a big party
for the farm workers.

251
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:11,240
You are celebrating
before the deal is even closed?

252
00:15:12,210 --> 00:15:13,990
We can certainly close it.

253
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,760
Everyone has been working
really hard lately,

254
00:15:17,460 --> 00:15:19,160
so it'd be nice to unwind a little.

255
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:20,800
- But...
- Hey.

256
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:23,220
Don't worry about it.

257
00:15:24,710 --> 00:15:26,400
Just come and have fun tonight.

258
00:15:28,490 --> 00:15:31,000
I... I have a friend's wedding to attend.

259
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:32,400
I'm really sorry.

260
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:42,450
Boss.

261
00:15:44,070 --> 00:15:45,610
I have something important to tell you.

262
00:16:19,820 --> 00:16:21,700
Whoa. These fermented soybeans look so good.

263
00:16:21,820 --> 00:16:22,880
Can I have a piece of this, Auntie?

264
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:24,430
- Hey, no!
- Oh?!

265
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,620
You can't eat that!

266
00:16:26,650 --> 00:16:28,140
What? Why not?

267
00:16:28,170 --> 00:16:30,060
It's not cooked yet.

268
00:16:30,090 --> 00:16:31,520
How long do I have to wait? I'm hungry.

269
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:36,830
Can I have this one, then?

270
00:16:39,260 --> 00:16:41,080
- Can I have it now?
- Let me help you.

271
00:16:42,220 --> 00:16:43,220
Let's get the spoons first.

272
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,210
Ow!

273
00:16:49,730 --> 00:16:51,060
Hey, you want to break your back or what?

274
00:16:53,790 --> 00:16:55,040
You're not mad at me anymore?

275
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,990
Hey, make it quick. It's heavy!

276
00:16:59,010 --> 00:16:59,650
Ow!

277
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:01,450
Saeng, I need your help.

278
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:02,520
Right, right.

279
00:17:04,990 --> 00:17:05,990
Here. Let me help you.

280
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:06,859
Oh?

281
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,589
What about Paula?

282
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:10,400
Where is she?

283
00:17:10,790 --> 00:17:12,720
Why isn't she coming to help?

284
00:17:18,660 --> 00:17:21,119
Alright. Let's do a makeover!

285
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,560
Going all out.

286
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,200
Guys, look at her.

287
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:06,320
Pawn is here.

288
00:18:06,370 --> 00:18:07,590
Not with that tone of voice.

289
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:13,940
Sheesh.

290
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:20,980
Stunned?

291
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:24,580
Who did the makeup for you?

292
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,340
Ta-daa!

293
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:33,000
No doubt it was you, Saitharn, my brother.

294
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:36,460
Thanks, Saitharn.

295
00:18:36,650 --> 00:18:37,690
Without your help,

296
00:18:37,740 --> 00:18:39,920
I wouldn't dare come back here.

297
00:18:41,530 --> 00:18:43,230
By the way, what do you call
that thing you do?

298
00:18:43,260 --> 00:18:46,210
Is it a 'maker'?

299
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,300
Make...

300
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,080
'Makeover'.

301
00:18:49,130 --> 00:18:49,990
- Yeah!
- Yes.

302
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:51,680
"Makeover."

303
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,880
A makeover,

304
00:18:56,950 --> 00:18:58,800
one to remember.

305
00:18:59,300 --> 00:18:59,940
Ever heard of it?

306
00:18:59,970 --> 00:19:00,780
No, I haven't.

307
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:01,890
Come, Saitharn.

308
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:03,450
Come and enjoy dinner with us here.

309
00:19:03,550 --> 00:19:04,740
Are you not going to invite me?

310
00:19:04,850 --> 00:19:06,430
Why should I?

311
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:07,200
Fine then.

312
00:19:07,260 --> 00:19:09,260
- I'll go show off my look to Bua and Auntie.
- Okay.

313
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,720
- Bye.
- Here, here.

314
00:19:13,850 --> 00:19:15,560
- Would you like to join me?
- Sure thing.

315
00:19:33,010 --> 00:19:34,210
- Good evening, Boss.
- Good evening.

316
00:19:43,020 --> 00:19:44,730
So refreshing.

317
00:20:04,170 --> 00:20:06,280
Our local moonshine is the real deal!

318
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:09,510
Now, hand over your cup!

319
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,070
Boss, would you like to have some?

320
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:16,500
A full shot for everyone, alright?

321
00:20:16,620 --> 00:20:18,440
No problem.

322
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:23,840
Alright!

323
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:25,020
Cheers!

324
00:20:36,530 --> 00:20:37,640
Don't hold back tonight!

325
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:39,080
Our lovely Boss

326
00:20:39,130 --> 00:20:41,040
literally bought out all the liquor for us!

327
00:20:43,620 --> 00:20:44,680
Tonight...

328
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:46,400
Can you please treat us to some drinks?

329
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:48,750
Good grief, I thought
it was something serious!

330
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:51,200
This is serious, Boss.

331
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:53,760
The party won't be as fun without drinks.

332
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:55,160
It must be the local moonshine, too!

333
00:20:57,370 --> 00:20:58,160
Please.

334
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:01,260
Boss.

335
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:02,600
Boss.

336
00:21:03,140 --> 00:21:05,070
I'll take that as a yes.

337
00:21:11,390 --> 00:21:13,030
- One more, Boss.
- More!

338
00:21:14,630 --> 00:21:15,420
Another shot?

339
00:21:20,770 --> 00:21:22,380
- Whoa, I'm getting hammered.
- Come on. Cheers.

340
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:24,640
I'm sobering up.

341
00:21:32,890 --> 00:21:34,680
Come here, yeah, cheers!

342
00:21:45,150 --> 00:21:45,820
Hey.

343
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:48,340
Are you drunk already?

344
00:21:49,740 --> 00:21:52,100
Drunk? This is my first one.

345
00:21:53,890 --> 00:21:54,800
And...

346
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:58,220
You don't call me Daddy anymore?

347
00:21:58,590 --> 00:21:59,260
Huh?

348
00:22:00,610 --> 00:22:02,280
Since when did I call you that?

349
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:06,190
Well...

350
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:09,470
You did when the two of us...

351
00:22:10,190 --> 00:22:11,320
Hold it right there.

352
00:22:11,650 --> 00:22:14,400
If you keep talking like a dirty old man,

353
00:22:14,430 --> 00:22:15,400
I'll leave.

354
00:22:15,420 --> 00:22:17,360
Oh, okay.

355
00:22:17,770 --> 00:22:19,120
I won't.

356
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:20,580
I'll stop now.

357
00:22:22,560 --> 00:22:23,960
Is that your first shot?

358
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:26,160
This is unexpected.

359
00:22:26,610 --> 00:22:29,740
I thought you would've already
chugged liters of the stuff.

360
00:22:31,990 --> 00:22:33,600
Oh, not so fast there.

361
00:22:34,170 --> 00:22:36,040
I wish I could do that,

362
00:22:36,890 --> 00:22:38,080
but the distilled liquor here

363
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:39,500
is really strong.

364
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,400
I need to hold back,

365
00:22:41,490 --> 00:22:43,350
or else I won't be able to work tomorrow.

366
00:22:44,670 --> 00:22:45,760
But look at you.

367
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,270
I didn't expect

368
00:22:47,690 --> 00:22:49,440
that you could actually drink
this kind of stuff.

369
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:52,640
I thought you only drink fancy aged wine.

370
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:54,880
Hey, you and your words.

371
00:22:55,510 --> 00:22:57,040
I'm a heavyweight drinker.

372
00:22:57,350 --> 00:22:58,440
Any liquor is fine by me.

373
00:22:59,380 --> 00:23:01,130
When I was your age,

374
00:23:02,420 --> 00:23:03,940
I'd been through it all.

375
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:10,930
The audacity.

376
00:23:11,050 --> 00:23:12,200
Who said they're a heavy drinker?

377
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:13,660
All I see is

378
00:23:14,010 --> 00:23:16,280
people getting drunk and blacking out.

379
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:18,310
Hey, now.

380
00:23:20,130 --> 00:23:21,180
So messy.

381
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:23,010
You're this old already, you know?

382
00:23:25,290 --> 00:23:26,240
No.

383
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:27,400
Listen.

384
00:23:27,930 --> 00:23:29,220
If my memory serves,

385
00:23:35,020 --> 00:23:35,920
you got drunk

386
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:37,450
and fell asleep on my chest.

387
00:23:37,530 --> 00:23:39,160
I remember it like it was yesterday.

388
00:23:39,810 --> 00:23:40,870
Me?

389
00:23:41,270 --> 00:23:42,610
It was you who was totally hammered.

390
00:23:42,790 --> 00:23:44,250
- No way.
- You fell asleep before I did.

391
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:46,110
No, it was you.

392
00:23:46,140 --> 00:23:47,050
It was you.

393
00:23:47,450 --> 00:23:48,900
- It was you.
- No, you.

394
00:23:48,940 --> 00:23:49,510
You.

395
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:50,250
You.

396
00:23:50,290 --> 00:23:51,120
- You.
- You.

397
00:23:51,150 --> 00:23:52,010
You.

398
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:53,080
You.

399
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:14,700
- Saitharn.
- Saitharn.

400
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:15,530
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

401
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:16,510
Right.

402
00:24:16,740 --> 00:24:17,930
- Okay, cheers!
- Cheers.

403
00:24:17,970 --> 00:24:18,510
Cheers.

404
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:20,280
Yay... yay.

405
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:21,810
Boss.

406
00:24:21,890 --> 00:24:23,070
- Huh?
- Can we do a toast with you?

407
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:24,510
Let's do it, Boss.

408
00:24:24,540 --> 00:24:26,170
Okay. Let's toast.

409
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:27,630
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

410
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:38,000
You seem to get along with everyone.

411
00:24:38,540 --> 00:24:40,060
Have you gotten used to being here?

412
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:46,990
Mm...

413
00:24:47,110 --> 00:24:47,760
I have.

414
00:24:49,750 --> 00:24:51,080
At first, I thought

415
00:24:52,470 --> 00:24:54,040
it wouldn't be all that great.

416
00:25:07,050 --> 00:25:07,800
Hey!

417
00:25:08,410 --> 00:25:10,360
What are you doing?!
Give me back my basket!

418
00:25:12,670 --> 00:25:15,400
But now that I've gotten
used to everyone here,

419
00:25:18,620 --> 00:25:20,870
it's far better than just...

420
00:25:20,930 --> 00:25:22,910
sitting around

421
00:25:23,460 --> 00:25:25,160
and doing nothing in Bangkok.

422
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:29,680
I'm planning to expand
my business by mid-next year.

423
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:31,800
It might not be as fun by then.

424
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:33,680
There'll be more work,

425
00:25:33,710 --> 00:25:35,480
and you will have to work a lot harder.

426
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:46,380
I probably won't be around by then.

427
00:26:01,830 --> 00:26:04,920
Do you plan to leave
after paying me all your debt?

428
00:26:15,710 --> 00:26:17,240
What other reasons

429
00:26:17,790 --> 00:26:19,320
do I have to stay here?

430
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:27,810
Me.

431
00:26:31,940 --> 00:26:34,440
Can I be the reason for you to stay?

432
00:26:52,630 --> 00:26:58,080
♫Not so ready to open up my heart♫

433
00:26:58,110 --> 00:27:01,670
♫Not so ready to feel anything yet♫

434
00:27:01,700 --> 00:27:05,560
♫No matter who came into my world♫

435
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:12,320
♫'Cause heart's been hurting for so long♫

436
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:15,950
♫It was never easy to start over♫

437
00:27:16,010 --> 00:27:20,410
♫Scared to feel that pain again ever♫

438
00:27:20,450 --> 00:27:23,230
♫I almost gave up on love♫

439
00:27:23,250 --> 00:27:28,160
♫I thought I would never find the right one♫

440
00:27:28,540 --> 00:27:33,970
♫But destiny led you to me♫

441
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,000
Ahh!

442
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:37,020
What are you doing sitting here?

443
00:27:37,060 --> 00:27:38,620
Come drink with us. Let's go!

444
00:27:38,660 --> 00:27:40,030
Come on, let's go have some drinks.

445
00:27:40,090 --> 00:27:42,140
What are you hanging
around Boss for? Come on.

446
00:27:42,180 --> 00:27:42,880
Let's go.

447
00:27:42,940 --> 00:27:44,550
We're off to have drinks now.

448
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:47,280
Drinks, drinks, drinks!

449
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:48,310
- Quickly.
- Right.

450
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,970
- Yay!
- Yeah!

451
00:27:50,050 --> 00:27:51,310
- Drink up!
- Drink.

452
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:56,480
If you have it, so do I.

453
00:28:46,290 --> 00:28:48,390
Auntie, don't stop now.
We're having fun.

454
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:50,840
- Get up, get up.
- Ow... I can't...

455
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:52,720
- Just go.
- Come on, just get up.

456
00:28:52,860 --> 00:28:53,860
Oh, oh.

457
00:28:53,970 --> 00:28:54,970
I guess I have to call you

458
00:28:55,190 --> 00:28:56,110
Grandma Nong now, don't I?

459
00:28:56,150 --> 00:28:57,170
Deary me, Wan!

460
00:28:57,700 --> 00:28:59,400
Watch your mouth,
or I'll knock you on the head.

461
00:28:59,430 --> 00:29:00,610
I'm sorry.

462
00:29:01,320 --> 00:29:02,840
Let her take a break for a bit.

463
00:29:03,230 --> 00:29:05,480
What if she starts babbling nonsense?

464
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:07,720
Gosh, this is no fun.

465
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:09,890
Let's go dance together, guys.

466
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:13,080
Gosh.

467
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:14,300
Look at Pawn.

468
00:29:14,330 --> 00:29:15,740
She was looking all pretty back there.

469
00:29:15,780 --> 00:29:17,400
Now, she's totally wasted.

470
00:29:19,100 --> 00:29:20,780
Would you like to head back and rest?

471
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:22,000
I'll walk you there.

472
00:29:22,020 --> 00:29:23,090
- Alright.
- One, two...

473
00:29:24,290 --> 00:29:25,440
Let's go.

474
00:29:45,700 --> 00:29:46,400
Oh?

475
00:29:46,630 --> 00:29:47,630
Auntie Nong!

476
00:29:47,910 --> 00:29:48,910
Ughh!!

477
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:50,500
- Huh?
- I was waiting for you.

478
00:29:51,050 --> 00:29:52,780
Ugh, wait for me too.

479
00:29:53,110 --> 00:29:55,940
I was waiting for a long, long time.

480
00:29:56,070 --> 00:29:58,440
Are you alright, Paula?
I'll take you home.

481
00:30:01,750 --> 00:30:03,400
Is this Saitharn?

482
00:30:03,660 --> 00:30:05,880
It really is you.

483
00:30:06,580 --> 00:30:08,540
My best friend.

484
00:30:10,440 --> 00:30:12,070
How was my accent?

485
00:30:12,130 --> 00:30:13,450
Is it good, yeah?

486
00:30:13,890 --> 00:30:14,890
Yeah, it's good.

487
00:30:19,330 --> 00:30:20,330
Right.

488
00:30:20,950 --> 00:30:23,760
You've been here for...

489
00:30:25,350 --> 00:30:26,670
a few weeks now, yeah?

490
00:30:28,370 --> 00:30:29,370
Do you like it here?

491
00:30:32,330 --> 00:30:33,330
Well,

492
00:30:33,570 --> 00:30:34,840
it's actually quite nice

493
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:36,220
now that I've settled in.

494
00:30:37,700 --> 00:30:39,200
But when I first got here,

495
00:30:45,330 --> 00:30:46,970
I had Saeng, Mok,

496
00:30:47,010 --> 00:30:49,160
and everyone to help
make things easier for me.

497
00:30:49,190 --> 00:30:51,240
I see.

498
00:30:51,580 --> 00:30:52,420
Eh...

499
00:30:52,560 --> 00:30:54,200
The "everyone" you mentioned

500
00:30:54,620 --> 00:30:56,520
includes me too, right?

501
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:00,540
Hey,

502
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:01,990
if you're not bored with this place,

503
00:31:02,030 --> 00:31:04,600
then stay with us as long as you can,

504
00:31:05,950 --> 00:31:06,600
alright?

505
00:31:06,730 --> 00:31:07,520
Well,

506
00:31:10,700 --> 00:31:13,040
I don't even know

507
00:31:14,190 --> 00:31:15,960
how long I'm going to stay here.

508
00:31:17,620 --> 00:31:19,100
Oh, come on!

509
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:21,400
What are you saying?

510
00:31:23,060 --> 00:31:24,640
Let me tell you something.

511
00:31:26,270 --> 00:31:27,730
You don't have to find an answer

512
00:31:28,310 --> 00:31:30,440
for everything.

513
00:31:30,810 --> 00:31:35,000
If you're happy here, then just stay.

514
00:31:36,140 --> 00:31:38,600
It doesn't matter if
you grew up here like me

515
00:31:39,100 --> 00:31:41,760
or just came here a few days ago.

516
00:31:44,690 --> 00:31:46,360
Auntie Nong once said,

517
00:31:46,590 --> 00:31:49,380
"If we share the same pot of rice,

518
00:31:49,580 --> 00:31:51,820
then we're pretty much family."

519
00:31:53,790 --> 00:31:54,980
Alright, brother?

520
00:32:01,420 --> 00:32:02,320
- Hey, don't move!
- Hey!

521
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:05,400
Let's go.

522
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:10,750
- Come here!
- Arghh!!

523
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:12,910
Paula, run!

524
00:32:12,940 --> 00:32:13,690
Run. Run!

525
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,120
Help me! Please help!

526
00:32:15,150 --> 00:32:16,280
Help me!

527
00:32:17,110 --> 00:32:18,040
Shut your mouth!

528
00:32:18,170 --> 00:32:19,020
Be quiet!!

529
00:32:21,250 --> 00:32:22,050
Don't move!

530
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:26,720
Ahh!!

531
00:32:38,630 --> 00:32:39,460
Ow!

532
00:32:45,500 --> 00:32:46,500
Hey!

533
00:32:48,940 --> 00:32:49,760
Paula...

534
00:32:50,630 --> 00:32:51,670
Ugh, let me go!

535
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:55,960
Saitharn...

536
00:32:56,230 --> 00:32:57,470
Help me...

537
00:33:03,750 --> 00:33:06,220
I can go by myself,
just go back to Wan.

538
00:33:06,960 --> 00:33:09,160
I don't want you to
pass out and not come back.

539
00:33:13,890 --> 00:33:14,660
Hey!

540
00:33:14,810 --> 00:33:15,840
Of all places,

541
00:33:15,900 --> 00:33:17,350
why are you peeing right next to me?!

542
00:33:19,310 --> 00:33:20,310
Go away.

543
00:33:20,350 --> 00:33:21,030
Hey...

544
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,160
Let me pee!

545
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:23,480
Go away.

546
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:26,300
Fine. Or do you want some of this?

547
00:33:27,780 --> 00:33:28,780
Yeah, yeah...

548
00:33:34,770 --> 00:33:35,400
Hey!

549
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:37,500
What?

550
00:33:38,270 --> 00:33:39,270
What are you doing?

551
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:41,820
- Hey, Pawn!
- Pawn!

552
00:33:41,850 --> 00:33:42,960
- Pawn!
- Pawn!

553
00:33:43,090 --> 00:33:44,130
- Pawn!
- Pawn!

554
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:45,800
- Wake up, Pawn.
- Pawn!

555
00:33:46,140 --> 00:33:47,220
Pawn, are you alright?

556
00:33:50,990 --> 00:33:51,960
Help...

557
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:53,640
Go help Saitharn.

558
00:33:54,180 --> 00:33:54,960
Saitharn...

559
00:33:56,450 --> 00:33:57,600
Saitharn...

560
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:59,400
Go get help as fast as you can.

561
00:33:59,580 --> 00:34:00,600
Pawn is injured.

